article.description: Alex Bentley scored 18 points to lead four players in double figures, and Penn State (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today, No. 18 AP) beat Northwestern 77-63 on Sunday.
article.headline: Alex Bentley propels Penn State to fourth straight victory
article.linkText: PSU drops Northwestern for fourth straight win
article.story:
EVANSTON, Ill. --  Alex Bentley scored 18 points to lead four players in double figures, and Penn State (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today, No. 18 AP) beat Northwestern 77-63 on Sunday.

The win was the fourth straight for the Lady Lions (20-5, 11-2 Big Ten). Zhaque Gray scored 17 points, Maggie Lucas had 11 and Nikki Greene added 10. Talia East had 10 rebounds off the bench.

Morgan Jones scored 20 points while Kendall Hackney added 15 for the Wildcats (13-12, 3-9). Northwestern, clad in all pink as part of a breast cancer awareness event, has lost three straight and six of its last seven.

Hackney had seven rebounds and topped 500 for her Northwestern career.
